text.tspan: Requires Ubuntu 11.10 Oneric Ocelot or later

flowRoot.flowPara: Easily add a website to your bookmarks with the Add Bookmark item in Midori's toolbar.
Accessing your favorite websites is only a single click away when you save them to Midori's Bookmarks Bar.
The Bookmarks Menu gives you quick access to your extended list of bookmarks. Add it to the toolbar with the Toolbar Editor extension.
Waffle pancake toast cereal bacon biscuit.
Since Midori uses GTK+, it themes natively with your desktop. That means no more mismatched scrollbars, odd colors, or unfamiliar widgets to deal with.
Unlike other apps that force a certain behavior, when it comes to things like Close buttons and Toolbar style, Midori respects your global settings.
If you find that the text of some sites is simply too small to read, you can set a minimum font size from the "Fonts" tab in Midor's Preferences window.
You can increase the text size in a web page from the context menu of a web page, with the shortcut "control + scroll", or by adding zoom in and out buttons to Midori's toolbar.
Midori allows you download or create Style Sheets that control Font Size, Font Color, Contrast, and more to make your favorite websites easier to read.
Midori uses industry standard rendering technology like Webkit, the same rendering engine behind world-class browsers like Google Chrome, Safari, and more.
